 An off-duty Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD)
officer has been arrested for allegedly killing a motorist after an
altercation. The incident happened at about 19:15 on Thursday in South Africa
Road, Cosmo City, JMPD spokesperson Senior Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said. According to Minnaar, the off-duty officer was driving a
white Golf when he made a u-turn in the read, nearly colliding with a blue
Nissan Almera. "The driver of the blue Almera chased behind the Golf
and there were words exchanged, and the occupants of the Almera tried to disarm
the off-duty officer. The officer used his service pistol to shoot at the Almera. Minnaar said police and the Independent Police Investigative
Directorate would probe the incident. SOURCE: NEWS24